==Estonian==

===Etymology===
From the Estonian verb ''[[tuhnima]]'' 'to [[burrow]], to [[dig]]'. 

===Noun===
'''tuhnik'''

# [[Aardvark]].  A mammalian genus (''[[Orycteropus]]''). 
# [[Aardvark]].  A mammalian species (''[[Orycteropus afer]]'').  ''Tuhnik [[peab]] [[saama]] [[kaapida]].''  The aardvark must have the possibility of digging.

===Conjugation===
*Singular genitive: [[tuhniku]]
*Singular partitive: [[tuhnikut]]
*Singular illative: [[tuhnikusse]]
*Plural nominative: [[tuhnikud]]
*Plural genitive: [[tuhnikute]]
*Plural partitive: [[tuhnikuid]]
*Plural illative: [[tuhnikutesse]], [[tuhnikuisse]]

